|-\n|St. Stephen\n|\n|601 Eucalyptus Dr\n|Parish formed in 1950; new church dedicated in 1964<ref>{{cite web|title=Excerpt from \"Saint Stephen Parish Celebrates Fifty Years\"|publisher=Saint Stephen Church|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://www.saintstephensf.org/our-history.php}}</ref>\n|-\n|St. Thomas More\n|\n|1300 Junipero Serra Blvd\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Home page|publisher=St. Thomas More Church|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://stmchurch.com/}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Deanery 2===\nDeanery 2 consists of the [[Bayview-Hunters Point, San Francisco|Bayview/Hunter's Point]] neighborhood, and the [[Excelsior District]], [[Visitacion Valley]], and [[Crocker Amazon]], and Ingleside areas.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:75%\"\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"25%\" |'''Name'''\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"10%\" |'''Image'''\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"25%\" |'''Location'''\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"15\" |'''Description/Notes'''\n|-\n|All Hallows Chapel\n|\t\n|1400 Newhall St\n|Historic church located on a hill overlooking [[Bayview\u2013Hunters Point, San Francisco|Hunters Point]]; now merged into the Our Lady of Lourdes parish<ref>{{cite web|title=History of Our Church|publisher=Our Lady of Lourdes - All Hallows Catholic Community|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://www.ourladyoflourdescatholicsf.org/history}}</ref>\n|-\n|Corpus Christi\n|\n|62 Santa Rosa Ave\n|A Salesian parish<ref>{{cite web|title=Home page|publisher=Corpus Christi Church|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://corpuschristisf.org/}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Church of the Epiphany in San Francisco|Church of the Epiphany]]\n|\n|827 Vienna St\n|Current church completed in 1950<ref>{{cite web|title=History of Our Parish|publisher=Church of the Epiphany|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://epiphanysf.com/history}}</ref>\n|-\n|Our Lady of Lourdes\n|\n|410 Hawes St\n|Wooden chapel 