history}}</ref>\n|-\n|St. Monica\n|\n|470 24th Ave\n|Parish dates to 1911; current church dedicated in 1918<ref>{{cite web|title=History of St. Monica Parish|publisher=Saint Monica-Saint Thomas the Apostle Parish|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=http://smstaparishsf.org/about/history/}}</ref>\n|-\n|St. Thomas the Apostle\n|\n|3835 Balboa St\n|First church built 1923, expanded 1930<ref>{{cite web|title=History of St. Thomas the ApostleParish|publisher=Saint Monica-Saint Thomas the Apostle Parish|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=http://smstaparishsf.org/about/history/}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[St. Vincent de Paul Church in San Francisco|St. Vincent de Paul]]\n|[[File:St. Vincent de Paul Church, San Francisco.jpg|100px]]\n|2320 Green St\n|Parish in Pacific Heights neighborhood formed in 1901; new church opened in 1913 became known as the \"Church of the Exposition\"<ref>{{cite web|title=The History of St. Vincent de Paul Church - San Francisco|publisher=St. Vincent de Paul Parish in San Francisco|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=http://www.svdpsf.org/history.html}}</ref>\n|-\n|Star of the Sea\n|\n|4420 Geary Blvd\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Home page|publisher=Star of the Sea Catholic Church|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://starparish.com/}}</ref>\n|-\n|Nativity of Our Lord\n|\n|240 Fell St\n|Dedicated in 1904, began as a parish serving the Croatian and Slovenian immigrants<ref>{{cite web|title=About Us|publisher=Nativity of Our Lord Roman Catholic Church|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=http://www.sfnativity.org/aboutus.html}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Deanery 4===\nDeanery 4 consists of San Francisco's Financial District, [[Chinatown]], [[North Beach, San Francisco, California|North Beach]], [[Tenderloin, San Francisco|Tenderloin District]], and [[South of Market, San Francisco, California|SOMA]] areas.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:75%\"\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"25%\" |'''Name'''\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"10%\" |''