{"title_page": "Nora Fatehi", "text_new": "{{short description|Canadian dancer, model, actress and singer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name        = Nora Ali\n| image       = Nora Ali at the trailer launch of Batla House.jpg\n| image_size  = 220px\n| caption     = Nora Fatehi at the trailer launch of Batla House in July 2019.\n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  =[[Quebec]], [[Canada]]\n| occupation  = {{hlist|Actress|model|dancer}}\n| known_for   = [[Bigg Boss (Hindi season 9)|Bigg Boss 9]]''\n| website     = \n}}\n'''Nora Fatehi '''(born 6 February 1992<ref>{{cite news |title=Rumoured couple Nora Fatehi, Angad Bedi share the same birthday; wish each other in the sweetest way possible - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/rumoured-couple-nora-fatehi-angad-bedi-share-the-same-birthday-wish-each-other-in-the-sweetest-way-possible/articleshow/57016419.cms |accessdate=3 January 2019 |work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/bigg-boss-9-contestant-nora-fatehi-dances-like-crazy-at-her-birthday-bash/|title=Bigg Boss 9 contestant Nora Fatehi dances like crazy at her birthday party|date=21 April 2016}}</ref>) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] dancer, model, actress and singer who has mainly appeared in [[Hindi]] films. She has also starred in [[Malayalam language|Malayalam]] and [[Telugu language|Telugu]] films. She comes from a [[Moroccan Canadians|Moroccan Canadian]] family, and was born and raised in [[Canada]], although in interviews despite being of Moroccan descent she has stated that she considers herself \"an Indian at heart\".<ref name=\"NoraNationality\">{{cite news |title=I'm an Indian at heart: Bigg Boss 9 contestant Nora Fatehi |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/im-an-indian-at-heart-bigg-boss-9-contestant-nora-fatehi/ |accessdate=3 January 2019 |work=The Indian Express |date=9 February 2016 }}</ref> She is most known for her work in the [[Cinema of India | Indian film industry]]. She made her film debut in the [[Bollywood]] film ''[[Roar: Tigers of the Sundarbans]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://roarthefilm.com/cast.html|title=ROAR : TIGERS OF THE SUNDARBANS OFFICIAL WEBSITE|publisher=roarthefilm.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/moroccan-model-nora-fatehi-debut-with-roar-tigers-of-the-sunderbans/1/395744.html|title=Make way for Moroccan model Nora Fatehi as she makes her debut with Roar|publisher=indiatoday.intoday.in}}</ref> She gained popularity in [[Telugu cinema]] by doing [[item number]]s in films like ''[[Temper (film)|Temper]], Beginning|Baahubali]] and [[Kick 2]]'' and has also starred in two Malayalam films, ''[[Double Barrel (film)|Double Barrel]]'' and ''[[Kayamkulam Kochunni (2018 film)|Kayamkulam Kochunni]]''. \n\nIn 2015, she was a contestant on the reality television show ''[[Bigg Boss (Hindi TV series)|Bigg Boss 9]]'' and was evicted on Day 84. In 2016, she participated in the reality television dance show ''[[Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa]]''. She appeared in the Bollywood film ''[[Satyameva Jayate (2018 film)|Satyamev Jayate]]'' in which she was seen in the recreated version of the song \"[[Dilbar (song)|Dilbar]]\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Dilbar - YouTube |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TRa9IMvccjg |website=www.youtube.com |accessdate=15 January 2019}}</ref> which crossed 20 million views on YouTube in the first 24 hours of its release, making it the first Hindi song to have garnered such numbers in India.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.music-asia.com/2018/07/satyameva-jayates-dilbar-breaks-records-in-india/|title=Satyameva Jayate's \"Dilbar\" breaks records in India|date=10 July 2018|work=Music Asia|access-date=21 July 2018|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180721221623/https://www.music-asia.com/2018/07/satyameva-jayates-dilbar-breaks-records-in-india/|archive-date=21 July 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> She also collaborated with the [[Morocco | Moroccan]] [[Hip hop | hip-hop]] group {{ill|Fna\u00efre|fr}} to release an [[Arabic]] version of the ''[[Dilbar (song)|Dilbar]]'' song.<ref>{{cite news |title=Nora Fatehi's Arabic version of Dilbar has set the internet on fire and how! Watch video {{!}} Bollywood News |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/nora-fatehis-arabic-version-of-dilbar-has-set-the-internet-on-fire-and-how-watch-video/324543 |work=www.timesnownews.com}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web |title=Dilbar Arabic Version - YouTube |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_108FB3SLuk |websitom |accessdate=15 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nFatehi began her career by appearing in a [[Bollywood]] film ''[[Roar: Tigers of the Sundarbans]]''. After that she was signed for an item number in [[Puri Jagannath]]'s [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film ''[[Temper (film)|Temper]]'', marking her debut in [[Telugu language|Telugu]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/NTR-dances-like-a-dream-Nora-Fatehi/articleshow/45435183.cms\"NTR|title=dances like a dream: Nora Fatehi\"|accessdate=12 January 2020}}</ref> She has also done a special appearance with [[Emraan Hashmi]] and Gurmeet Chaudhary in the film ''[[Mr. X (2015 film)|Mr. X]]'' directed by [[Vikram Bhatt]] and produced by [[Mahesh Bhatt]].\n\nLater Fatehi appeared in item numbers for movies such as ''[[Baahubali: The Beginning]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/nora-fatehi-signed-for-a-special-song-in-baahubali/536504-8-66.html|title=Nora Fatehi signed for a special song in 'Baahubali'|work=IBNLive}}</ref> and ''[[Kick 2]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Nora-Fatehi-to-groove-with-Ravi-Teja-in-Kick-2/articleshow/46849131.cms|title=Nora Fatehi to groove with Ravi Teja in Kick 2|work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/south-gossip/after-grooving-with-jr-ntr-noorah-fatehi-to-shake-a-leg-with-ravi-teja-in-kick-2/|title=After grooving with Jr NTR, Noorah Fatehi to shake a leg with Ravi Teja in Kick 2?|publisher=bollywoodlife.com|date=7 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn late June 2015, she signed a Telugu film ''[[Sher (film)|Sher]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/nora-fatehi-item-song-in-kalyan-ram-sher-telugu-news-136368.html|title=Kalyan Ram with 'Temper' girl|publisher=indiaglitz.com}}</ref> In late August 2015, she signed a Telugu film ''[[Loafer (2015 film)|Loafer]]'' which is directed by [[Puri Jagannadh]] starring opposite [[Varun Tej]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/nora-fathehi-in-a-special-number-in-loafer-telugu-news-140800.html%22Nora|title=- Telugu News|website=IndiaGlitz.com}}</ref> In late November 2015 she signed a film ''[[Oopiri]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Nora-Fatehis-item-song-will-add-a-desi-tadka-to-the-Intouchables-remake/articleshow/49909012.cms\"Nora|title=Fatehi's item song will add a desi tadka to the Intouchables remake\"|accessdate=12 January 2020}}</ref> In December 2015, Fatehi entered the [[Bigg Boss]] house which was in its [[Bigg Boss 9|ninth season]] as a wild card entrant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/brunch/bigg-boss-is-just-entertainment-shouldn-t-be-taken-so-seriously-nora-fatehi-s-secrets/story-dPX6UB9HKjFGdM46kaEWXN.html|title=Bigg Boss is just entertainment, shouldn't be taken so seriously: Nora Fatehi's secrets|date=30 September 2017|website=Hindustan Times}}</ref> She spent 3 weeks inside the house until she got evicted in the 12th week (Day 83). She was also contestant on ''[[Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa]]'' in 2016. She starred in ''[[My Birthday Song]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://themoviean.com/nora-fatehi-interview/ |title=From Bigg Boss to Bollywood |publisher= The Moviean|date=14 January 2018 }}</ref> in which she is playing lead actress opposite [[Sanjay Suri]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://crunknews.com/my-birthday-song-movie-wiki-cast-crew-story-poster-trailer/|title=My Birthday Song Movie Wiki Cast Crew Story Poster Trailer|first=Sangra|last=Ankush|date=23 December 2017|access-date=23 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180417030838/http://crunknews.com/my-birthday-song-movie-wiki-cast-crew-story-poster-trailer/|archive-date=17 April 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2019, she signed a contract with the record label [[T-Series (company) | T-Series]] as an exclusive artist, and will feature on their upcoming films, music videos, web series, and web movies.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Desk |first1=IBT Entertainment |title=Nora Fatehi exclusively signed by T-Series |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/nora-fatehi-exclusively-signed-by-t-series-791256 |accessdate=5 February 2019 |work=International Business Times, India Edition |date=3 February 2019 |language=English}}</ref> She then appeared in the 2020 [[dance film]] ''[[Street Dancer 3D]]''.<ref name=\"Street3D\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\n[[File:Nora Fatehi graces the red carpet for Umang police show (07) (cropped).jpg|thumb|Fatehi at an event in 2017]]\n[[File:Nora Fatehi snapped at Krome studio in Bandra.jpg|thumb|Fatehi at Krome Studio in [[Bandra]] in March 2019]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#FFFFCC;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n!scope=\"col\"|  Year\n!scope=\"col\"|  Film\n!scope=\"col\"|  Language(s)\n!scope=\"col\"|  Role(s)\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|  Notes\n|-\n|2014 ||''[[Roar: Tigers of the Sundarbans]]'' ||[[Hindi]] || CJ ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"8\"|2015 ||''[[Crazy Cukkad Family]]''||Hindi ||Amy ||\n|-\n|''[[Temper (film)|Temper]]'' || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] ||  ||Special